  "text": "Given two or more sets of observations, the main problem is how to identify which separate sets of data belong to the same physical object (the so-called correlation problem). Thus the orbit determination problem needs to be solved in two stages: first different sets of observations need to be correlated, then an orbit can be determined; this combined procedure is called linkage in the literature [CITATION_1] .",
